                  <h6 class="caption-text__heading">Relation between maximum FRET response and expression levels of donor and acceptor fluorophores.</h6>
                
                
                <div class="caption-text__body"><p class="paragraph">(<b>a</b>) (Left) Scatter plot with donor intensity (<i>D</i>, green) versus FRET response to 500 M MeAsp (<i>D</i>) and (right) acceptor intensity (<i>A</i>, red, measured by direct excitation) with marginal distributions for <i>A</i>, <i>D</i> and <i>D</i> in VS104/pSJAB12. For the donor intensity we measured at low induction (10 M IPTG, dark green) and high induction (100 M IPTG, light green). The acceptor intensities were only measured at high induction. In the scatter plots the mean FRET response is plotted with the error bars (blue), the horizontal line indicating the average for the binned data as described in panel (<b>b</b>). The yellow curve is a fit to a gamma distribution with corresponding values and 95% confidence intervals of <math id="inf87"><mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0"><mrow><mi>k</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>2.0</mn><mo></mo><mn>0.4</mn></mrow></mstyle></math> and <math id="inf88"><mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0"><mrow><mi></mi><mo>=</mo><mn>10.2</mn><mo></mo><mn>2.5</mn></mrow></mstyle></math>. All fluorescent intensities are measured in photons/pixel, are divided by cell size (area) and corrected for inhomogeneous illumination. All histograms are normalized to the number of cells. (<b>b</b>) Gating of the data. Scatter plot of donor intensity versus acceptor intensity. All data with fluorescent intensities (in photons/pixel) lower than <i>D</i>=750 or <i>A</i>=175 are excluded from the analysis since the FRET response depends on donor and acceptor intensity levels below these levels. The distribution of the FRET response (extreme left) is only for the gated data.</p>
