                  <h6 class="caption-text__heading">Phosphorylation feedback is not a necessary condition for fast removal adaptation dynamics.</h6>
                
                
                <div class="caption-text__body"><p class="paragraph">Population FRET time series of cells expressing CheB-WT (orange), CheB-D56E (purple) , CheBc (green) in CheB (VS124) background as well as WT (CheB from native chromosome position, VS104, brown) are shown after removal of 500 M to which cells have adapted. The strain expressing CheB<math id="inf111"><mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0"><mrow><msup><mrow/><mrow><mtext>D56E</mtext></mrow></msup></mrow></mstyle></math> lacks phosphorylation feedback but has a fast removal response. The population FRET experiment is performed as described previously (<a href="/articles/27455#bib91">Sourjik and Berg, 2002a</a>). The strains and induction levels are the same as in the single-cell FRET experiments on the CheB mutants.</p>
